  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0dd6\u0dbd\u0dcf, \u0db6\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dc3\u0ddc\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0ddd \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0dc0\u0dc1\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dab \u0dc3\u0da7\u0db1\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Lula, Bolsonaro officially in the election battle",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President Jair Bolsonaro and his front-runner challenger Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva have officially kicked off Brazil's hottest October election in decades.",
        "\"Our country no longer needs corruption, it needs order and prosperity,\" Bolsonaro, a former army captain, told a crowd at Ju\u00eds de Fora on Tuesday afternoon, recalling his stab at the 2018 campaign that swept him to power and fueled anti-Lula sentiment. having done",
        "His supporters were said to have chanted \"Lula the thief\" during his speech.",
        "Nine years older than his opponent, Lula, 76, began his campaign by stopping at the gates of the Volkswagen car factory outside Sao Paulo amid repression under the military dictatorship.",
        "In a video posted on social media Tuesday morning, Lula said hunger has returned to Brazil under Bolsonaro and inflation is hitting families who cannot survive on the minimum wage.",
        "\"We have a lot of work to do to get this country back together,\" he said as he launched his bid to return to office. \"I want to be president again to change people's lives, because nobody can take it the way it is anymore.\""
      ],
